Canada Accepts 19 Cuban Political Prisoners
OTTAWA , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- Canadian Prime Minister Jean Chretien announced Thursday that the Cuban government has agreed to let 19 Cuban political prisoners come to Canada .
The 19 prisoners have agreed to come to Canada as a condition of their release , Chretien said in a news release .
" The decision to release these prisoners demonstrate the benefits of a policy of construction engagement with Cuba on a broad range of issues , including sensitive political ones , " Chretien said .
Immigration processing of the 19 individuals will begin immediately , the government said .
